100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 9, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, deliberating on disarmament and international peace, amidst ongoing tensions in Europe. In the United States, a significant cold snap gripped the Midwest, with temperatures plunging to record lows, disrupting daily life and transportation. Meanwhile, in Britain, the government faced mounting pressure regarding unemployment as workers continued to struggle in the post-war economy.
